{"id":21793,"date":"2017-11-23T22:24:41","date_gmt":"2017-11-24T06:24:41","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/coertvonk.com\/?p=21793"},"modified":"2022-04-18T20:43:29","modified_gmt":"2022-04-19T03:43:29","slug":"21793","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"http:\/\/coertvonk.com\/sw\/filters-sw\/21793-21793","title":{"rendered":"FIR filter using trigonometry"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>    \r\n    \\(\\)Studies the response to a general sinusoid input to a simple FIR filter using trigonometry.  Assume a general sinusoid input \\(x[n]=A\\cos(\\omega nT+\\phi)\\) with amplitude \\(A\\) and phase \\(\\phi\\).  The filter phase response does not depend on \\(\\phi\\) due to time-invariance, so we can set \\(\\phi=0\\).  The filter gain doesn&#8217;t depend on the \\(A\\) due to linearity, so we get set \\(A=1\\)\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"flex-container math\">\r\n        $$\r\n            y[n]=x[n]+x[n-1]=\\cos(\\omega nT)+\\cos(\\omega (n-1)T)\r\n        $$\r\n    <\/div>\r\n<\/p>\r\n<p>\r\n    Use trigonometry identities to reduce the expression\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"flex-container math\">\r\n        $$\r\n            \\begin{align}\r\n                y[n]=x[n]+x[n-1]&#038;=\\cos(\\omega nT)+\\cos(\\omega (n-1)T)\\nonumber\\\\\r\n                &#038;=\\cos(\\omega nT)+\\cos(\\omega nT)\\cos(-\\omega T)-\\sin(\\omega nT)\\sin(-\\omega T)\\nonumber\\\\\r\n                &#038;=\\cos(\\omega nT)+\\cos(\\omega nT)\\cos(\\omega T)+\\sin(\\omega nT)\\sin(\\omega T)\\nonumber\\\\\r\n                &#038;=\\underbrace{\\big(1+\\cos(\\omega T)\\big)}_{a(\\omega)}\\cos(\\omega nT)+\\underbrace{\\sin(\\omega nT)}_{b(\\omega)}\\sin(\\omega T)\r\n            \\end{align}\r\n        $$\r\n    <\/div>\r\n<\/p>\r\n<p>\r\n    Work towards a form with gain \\(G\\) and phase \\(\\varphi\\)\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"flex-container math\">\r\n        $$\r\n            \\begin{align}\r\n                y[n]&#038;=G(\\omega)\\cos\\big( \\omega nT+\\varphi(w) \\big) \\nonumber \\\\\r\n                &#038;=G(\\omega)\\cos\\big(\\varphi(w) \\big)\\cos(\\omega nT)-G(\\omega)\\sin\\big(\\varphi(w) \\big)\\sin(\\omega nT)\r\n            \\end{align}\r\n        $$\r\n    <\/div>\r\n<\/p>\r\n<p>\r\n    Substitute\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"flex-container math\">\r\n        $$\r\n            \\begin{split}\r\n                {a(\\omega)}\\cos(\\omega nT)+{b(\\omega)}\\sin(\\omega T) =\r\n                G(\\omega)\\cos\\big(\\varphi(w) \\big)\\cos(\\omega nT)\\\\\r\n                -G(\\omega)\\sin\\big(\\varphi(w) \\big)\\sin(\\omega nT)\r\n            \\end{split}\r\n            \\nonumber\r\n        $$\r\n    <\/div>\r\n    <div class=\"flex-container math\">\r\n        $$\r\n            \\implies\r\n            \\left\\{\r\n                \\begin{aligned}\r\n                    a(\\omega)&#038;=G(\\omega)\\cos\\big(\\varphi(w) \\big)\\nonumber\\\\\r\n                    b(\\omega)&#038;=G(\\omega)\\sin\\big(\\varphi(w) \\big)\r\n                \\end{aligned}\r\n            \\right.\r\n        $$\r\n    <\/div>\r\n<\/p>\r\n\r\n<h2>\r\n    Gain\r\n<\/h2>\r\n<p>\r\n    The filter gain (amplitude response) follows as\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"flex-container math\">\r\n        $$\r\n            \\begin{align}\r\n                a^2(\\omega)+b^2(\\omega)\r\n                &#038;= G^2(\\omega)\\cos^2\\big(\\varphi(w) \\big)+\r\n                G^2(\\omega)\\sin^2\\big(\\varphi(w) \\big)\\nonumber\\\\\r\n                &#038;= G^2(\\omega)\\Big(\\underbrace{\\cos^2\\big(\\varphi(w) \\big)+\r\n                \\sin^2\\big(\\varphi(w) \\big)}_{=1}\\Big)&#038;\\overset{\\sin^2\\alpha+\\cos^2\\alpha=1}{\\implies} \\nonumber \\\\\r\n                &#038;= G^2(\\omega)\r\n            \\end{align}\r\n        $$\r\n    <\/div>\r\n<\/p>\r\n<p>\r\n    Substitute \\(a(\\omega)\\) and \\(b(\\omega)\\)\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"flex-container math\">\r\n        $$\r\n            \\require{cancel}\r\n            \\begin{align}\r\n                G^2(\\omega)\r\n                &#038;=a^2(\\omega)+b^2(\\omega)\\nonumber\\\\\r\n                &#038;=\\big(1+\\cos(\\omega T)\\big)^2+\\sin^2(\\omega T)\\nonumber\\\\\r\n                &#038;=\\big(1+\\cos(\\omega T)\\big)^2+\\sin^2(\\omega T)\\nonumber\\\\\r\n                &#038;=\\big(1+2\\cos(\\omega T)+{\\cos^2(\\omega T)}\\big)+{\\sin^2(\\omega T)}&#038;\\overset{\\sin^2\\alpha+\\cos^2\\alpha=1}{\\implies}\\nonumber\\\\\r\n                &#038;=1+2\\cos(\\omega T)&#038;\\overset{\\cos^2\\alpha=\\frac{1}{2}(1+\\cos2\\alpha)}{\\implies}\\nonumber\\\\\r\n                &#038;=4\\cos^2\\left(\\frac{\\omega T}{2}\\right)\\nonumber\\\\\r\n            \\end{align}\r\n        $$\r\n    <\/div>\r\n<\/p>\r\n<p>\r\n    The gain follows as\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"flex-container math\">\r\n        $$\r\n            G(\\omega)=2\\left|\\cos\\left(\\frac{\\omega T}{2}\\right)\\right|\r\n        $$\r\n    <\/div>\r\n<\/p>\r\n<p>\r\n    Since \\(\\cos\\left(\\frac{\\omega T}{2}\\right)=\\cos(\\pi fT)\\) is positive for \\(-\\frac{f_s}{2}\\leq f\\leq\\frac{f_s}{2}\\), it is not necessary to take absolute value\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"flex-container math\">\r\n        $$\r\n            \\begin{align}\r\n                G(\\omega)=2\\cos\\left(\\frac{\\omega T}{2}\\right),&#038;&#038;|f|\\leq \\frac{f_s}{2}\r\n            \\end{align}\r\n        $$\r\n    <\/div>\r\n<\/p>\r\n\r\n<h2>\r\n    Phase\r\n<\/h2>\r\n<p>\r\n    The filter phase response \\(\\varphi(\\omega)\\) can be found as\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"flex-container math\">\r\n        $$\r\n            \\frac{b(\\omega)}{a(\\omega)}=-\\frac{\\cancel{G(\\omega)}\\sin\\big(\\varphi(\\omega)\\big)}{\\cancel{G(\\omega)}\\cos\\big(\\varphi(\\omega)\\big)}=-tan\\big(\\varphi(\\omega)\\big)\r\n        $$\r\n    <\/div>\r\n<\/p>\r\n<p>\r\n    Substituting the values of \\(a(\\omega)\\) and \\(b(\\omega)\\)\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"flex-container math\">\r\n        $$\r\n            \\begin{align}\r\n                \\tan\\big(\\varphi(\\omega)\\big)\r\n                &#038;=-\\frac{\\sin(\\omega T)}{1+cos(\\omega T)}\\nonumber\\\\\r\n                &#038;=-\\frac{2\\sin\\left(\\frac{\\omega T}{2}\\right)\\cos\\left(\\frac{\\omega T}{2}\\right)}{1+\\Big(\\cos^2\\left(\\frac{\\omega T}{2}\\right)-\\sin^2\\left(\\frac{\\omega T}{2}\\right)\\Big)}&#038;\\overset{\\sin2\\alpha=2\\sin\\alpha\\cos\\alpha}{\\implies}\\nonumber\\\\\r\n                &#038;=-\\frac{\\cancel{2}\\sin\\left(\\frac{\\omega T}{2}\\right)\\cancel{\\cos\\left(\\frac{\\omega T}{2}\\right)}}{\\cancel{2}\\cos^\\cancel{2}\\left(\\frac{\\omega T}{2}\\right)}\\nonumber\\\\\r\n                &#038;=\\tan\\left(-\\frac{\\omega T}{2}\\right)\r\n            \\end{align}\r\n        $$\r\n    <\/div>\r\n<\/p>\r\n<p>\r\n    The phase response follows as\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"flex-container math\">\r\n        $$\r\n            \\begin{align}\r\n                \\varphi(\\omega) &#038;=-\\frac{\\omega T}{2}\r\n            \\end{align}\r\n        $$\r\n    <\/div>\r\n<\/p>\r\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"Studies the response to a general sinusoid input.","protected":false},"author":41,"featured_media":0,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"closed","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"inline_featured_image":false,"_mi_skip_tracking":false},"categories":[405],"tags":[],"yoast_head":"<!-- This site is optimized with the Yoast SEO plugin v18.6 - https:\/\/yoast.com\/wordpress\/plugins\/seo\/ -->\n<title>FIR filter using trigonometry - Coert Vonk<\/title>\n<meta name=\"description\" content=\"Studies the response to a general sinusoid input to a simple FIR filter using trigonometry.\" \/>\n<meta name=\"robots\" content=\"index, follow, max-snippet:-1, max-image-preview:large, max-video-preview:-1\" \/>\n<link rel=\"canonical\" href=\"https:\/\/coertvonk.com\/sw\/filters-sw\/21793-21793\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:locale\" content=\"en_US\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:type\" content=\"article\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:title\" con